 "bear": {
  "claim": "The dossier is describing a memory-cycle top with historic amplitude: +346% revenue YoY and 68% net margins are peak prints for a business that showed 4.9% net margin eight quarters ago, and 6.0x forward earnings is exactly what memory names trade at when the E is about to collapse.",
  "pillars": [
   "The cycle signature is in the dossier's own history: net margin 4.9% (2024-05) -> 68.1% (2026-05) - a 14x margin swing in two years is amplitude, not structure, and amplitude mean-reverts in memory every time in the series.",
   "A $1.02 TRILLION market cap at 11.3x trailing sales prices the supercycle as permanent; if net margin merely reverts to the 38% of 2025-11, the same price is ~17x that earnings base before any multiple compression.",
   "Low forward P/E is the classic memory-top tell, not a value signal: 6.0x forward with PEG 0.14 says consensus itself cannot make the current earnings level grow - the market is refusing to capitalize peak margins, which is how every prior cycle top was priced.",
   "The +64.4% mean target and +673% momentum are the same crowd: when 42 analysts and an A- momentum grade agree at rank 1 of 201, the marginal buyer is already in the book."
  ],
  "catalysts": [
   "Next 2 quarters: first sequential HBM/DRAM price softness headline - at 91% above the 200-day the air pocket is large.",
   "H1 2027: supply response - every prior memory cycle in the 8-quarter dossier window ended with capacity catching demand.",
   "Any quarter: revenue growth printing below +100% YoY after +346% - deceleration at this amplitude reads as the turn."
